    comment: '<p>To vertically center block elements of known height:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">.vertical-center {\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 50%;\n  height: 400px;\n  margin-top: -200px;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can check out the evolution here:</p>\n<p><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><svg width="100%" height="auto" viewBox="0 0 810 310" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny"><desc>Created by HiQPdf</desc><defs></defs><g fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill-rule="evenodd" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" ><g fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8,8 L808,8 L808,308 L8,308 L8,8"/></g><g fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8,158 L808,158 L808,159 L8,159 L8,158"/></g><g fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M408,8 L409,8 L409,308 L408,308 L408,8"/></g><g fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M78,158 L398,158 L398,298 L78,298 L78,158"/></g><g fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="#596193" stroke-opacity="1" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><text fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" xml:space="preserve" x="78" y="239" font-family="&#x27;Roboto&#x27;,sans-serif" font-size="32" font-weight="400" font-style="normal" >top:50%;</text></g><g fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M418,88 L738,88 L738,228 L418,228 L418,88"/></g><g fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="#596193" stroke-opacity="1" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><text fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" xml:space="preserve" x="418" y="150" font-family="&#x27;Roboto&#x27;,sans-serif" font-size="32" font-weight="400" font-style="normal" >top:50%;</text></g><g fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="#596193" stroke-opacity="1" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><text fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" xml:space="preserve" x="418" y="187" font-family="&#x27;Roboto&#x27;,sans-serif" font-size="32" font-weight="400" font-style="normal" >margin-top: -height/2;</text></g></g></svg></p>\n<p><code>top: 50%</code> will put the top of the element in the center of its parent. <code>margin-top: -200px</code> will make the content of the element start 200px before its top. By combining both, we manage to center an element of known height.</p>\n',
